<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="b30Jan1939"><font color="red">30 January 1939</font> <i>NLFF</i> (from Paul L&eacute;on to Richard de la Mere): The book has just arrived &hellip; On my coming home I telephoned you &hellip; the first addition: Trothed today, trenned tomorrow.  can come as a separate sentence on page 486 line 10 from foot after the sentence ending with the word &ldquo;essaying&rdquo;. The second addition: Today&apos;s truth, tomorrow&apos;s trend. will come in the place indicated in my previous letter. This settles the book and there won&apos;t be any more corrections forthcoming. </div>
